## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-119">Телефоны, буквы или символы, которые описывают звуки речи.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-119">Phones are letters or symbols that describe the sounds of speech.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-120">System.Speech поддерживает три буквы фонетического для указания пользовательского Произношение: универсальной Phone набор (ИБП), набор Phone API речи (SAPI) и международного фонетического алфавита (IPA).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-120">System.Speech supports three phonetic alphabets for specifying custom pronunciations: the Universal Phone Set (UPS), the Speech API (SAPI) Phone set, and the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-121">Телефоны, указанный в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> должно соответствовать фонетического алфавита, указанный в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-121">The phones specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> must match the phonetic alphabet specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.PhoneticAlphabet%2A>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-122">В разделе [словари и алфавитах фонетического](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/435e3c6f-6834-4e5a-b0f6-c17b2275dc51) для получения дополнительной информации.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-122">See [Lexicons and Phonetic Alphabets](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/435e3c6f-6834-4e5a-b0f6-c17b2275dc51) for more information.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-123">Телефоны, указанный в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> указать, как содержимое <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> следует произносится для распознавания успешно.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-123">The phones specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> indicate how the contents of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> should be pronounced for successful recognition.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-124">Распознавание речи использует произношение, указанный в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> в соответствии с речевого ввода и возвращает строку, содержащихся в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> в результате распознавания.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-124">The speech recognition engine uses the pronunciation specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> to match speech input and returns the string contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A> in the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-125">Если телефоны не разделяются пробелами или указанная строка содержит нераспознанный телефона, механизм распознавания не распознает указанного произношение, что допустимый произношение слова, содержащиеся в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-125">If the phones are not space-delimited or the specified string contains an unrecognized phone, the recognition engine does not recognize the specified pronunciation as a valid pronunciation of the word contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-126">Произношения, указанный в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> имеют приоритет над произношение, указанный в словари, связанной с Грамматика или механизма распознавания.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-126">Pronunciations specified in <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> take precedence over pronunciations specified in lexicons associated with a grammar or a recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-127">Кроме того, произношение в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> свойство применимо только к одним вхождением слова или фразы, содержащиеся в <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-127">Also, the pronunciation in the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> property applies only to the single occurrence of the word or phrase contained by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Text%2A>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-128">Грамматики в следующем примере содержит обзор содержит описание различных слов и также имеет необычное слова: «whatchamacallit».</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-128">The grammar in the following example contains slang words and also has an uncommon word: "whatchamacallit".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-129">Добавление пользовательской, произношение встроенные с использованием <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> свойство <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> класса может повысить точность распознавания со словом «whatchamacallit» также и для всего фразу, которая его содержит.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-129">Adding a custom, inline pronunciation using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken.Pronunciation%2A> property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsToken> class can improve the accuracy of recognition for the word "whatchamacallit" as well as for the entire phrase that contains it.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="7ae19-130">В примере телефоны из Microsoft универсальной Phone набор (ИБП) используется для определения пользовательских произношения.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="7ae19-130">The example uses phones from the Microsoft Universal Phone Set (UPS) to define the custom pronunciations.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize an instance of the in-process recognizer.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Build the SrgsOneOf objects with alternative choices for the slang phrase.  
        SrgsOneOf gimme = new SrgsOneOf(  
          new string[] { "give me", "gimme", "hand me", "ha'me" });  
        SrgsOneOf the = new SrgsOneOf(new string[] { "the", "duh" });  
  
        // Build the one-of element that contains the pronunciation.  
        SrgsItem thing = new SrgsItem("thingamajig");  
        SrgsItem whatcha = new SrgsItem();  
        SrgsToken callit = new SrgsToken("whatchamacallit");  
        callit.Pronunciation = "W AE T CH AE M AE K AA L IH T";  
        whatcha.Add(callit);  
        SrgsOneOf what = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {thing, whatcha});  
  
        // Create the rule from the SrgsOneOf objects.  
        SrgsRule slangRule = new SrgsRule("slang", gimme, the, what);  
  
        // Build an SrgsDocument object from the rule and set the phonetic alphabet.  
        SrgsDocument tokenPron = new SrgsDocument(slangRule);  
        tokenPron.PhoneticAlphabet = SrgsPhoneticAlphabet.Ups;  
  
        // Create a Grammar object from the SrgsDocument and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g_Slang = new Grammar(tokenPron);  
        g_Slang.Name = ("Slang Pronunciation");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g_Slang);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=   
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start asynchronous recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Handle the SpeechRecognized event.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Recognized phrase: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine("Confidence: " + e.Result.Confidence);  
      Console.WriteLine("  Word summary: ");  
      foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in e.Result.Words)  
      {  
        Console.WriteLine(  
          "    Lexical form ({1})" +  
          " Pronunciation ({0})" +  
          " Confidence ({2})",  
          word.Pronunciation, word.LexicalForm, word.Confidence);  
      }  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```
